    What is difference between selenium and Cypress?
    Selenium is a legacy system that has been around for a long time, since 2002. Selenium has a huge install base and is more widely used than any other automation testing tool. Cypress is newer and gaining in popularity. Cypress is fast for API, front-end, and end-to-end testing, thanks to its architectural differences.19-Aug-2022
